Install GHCup: Open your terminal and run curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://get-ghcup.haskell.org | sh

Add to PATH: After installation, add GHCup to your PATH by running export PATH="$HOME/.ghcup/bin:$PATH". To make this permanent, add the same line to your ~/.bashrc file and run source ~/.bashrc.

Install VS Code Extension: In VS Code, go to Extensions (Ctrl+Ctrl+X), search for "Haskell" (from Haskell), and install it.

Configure Code Runner: If you use the Code Runner extension, go to Settings (Ctrl+,), search for code-runner.runInTerminal, and check
the box to enable it for interactive input.

"undefined reference" error (-lgmp): Install the math library with sudo dnf install gmp-devel.

"command not found" error (ghc or runghc): Ensure ~/.ghcup/bin is in your PATH by running export PATH="$HOME/.ghcup/bin:$PATH".
